Beautiful Marlin 336 CS, flawless and like new. The pictures don't do it justice. title: For Sale:  Rare American Arms Fox Model Side Load Double Barrel Shotgun
postcontent: This is a VERY rare American Arms Fox Model Side Load Shotgun. This gun was in the collection of a Jewelry store many years ago in this town sitting in the case pictured and now after all these years is up for sale. These guns are a unique "swing breech" design patented by George H Fox and were manufactured between the years 1870-1884 with a low production of possibly less than 5,000 according to some sources. They came in either 10 Gauge or 12 Gauge and lengths of barrels measured 26, 28, 30 and 32. This gun has a barrel length of 28 and I was told is in 12 Gauge. The stock is cracked and I did not remove the tape to see how bad but I assume it will need repaired or replaced. The barrel is clean on the outside with only a minor ding towards the end and the bore of the shotgun does have some surface rust and pitting. I did not attempt to clean and feel that should be left more for the professional. Action works smooth and locks up tight, hammers cock and activate as they should and the gun still presents very well and is a great conversation piece. These guns sell for very high dollar and have a high book. I am offering this gun for $500 which I think is fair to the collector of interesting and unique historical firearms. The Red Head gun case that the rifle was found in, comes with it. Buyer will pay all shipping fees and please email with any additional questions you may have or request for pics. Gun is an antique and is safe to ship but please know your local laws regarding antiques. Gun should not be fired unless checked out by a competent gunsmith.

LSB#: 120828SK01

Make: High Standard

Model: Sentinel Model R-101

Serial Number: 607639

Year of Manufacture: 1956

Caliber: .22 Short, Long or Long Rifle

Action Type: Single or Double Action with Swing-Out Cylinder

Markings: The left side of the barrel is marked “Hi-Standard / .22 Cal”. The left side of the frame has a medallion with a “Hi-Standard” logo and marked “Sentinel”. The right side of the barrel is marked “High Standard Mfg. Corp. / Hamden, Conn. U.S.A.”and the right side of the frame is marked “R-101 / 607639”.

Barrel Length: 6”

Sights / Optics: The revolver is mounted with a flat topped square notched rear sight dovetailed into the barrel and a blade front side.

Stock Configuration & Condition: The grip is one piece checkered brown plastic. The grips show minor handling marks and has mars in the checkering. The grip screw shows erosion. The grips rate in about Very Good overall condition.

Type of Finish: The barrel and cylinder are blued steel while the alloy frame has a matte black finish.

Finish Originality: All Original

Bore Condition: The bore is shiny and the rifling is a little shallow. There is no erosion.

Overall Condition: This revolver retains about 50% of its metal finish. The top of the front and rear sights show wear. The front half of the barrel shows wear and thinning, as does the cylinder. The frame shows wear and frosting, and there are a few small spots of pinprick surface erosion on the hammer. The markings are clear. Overall, this revolver rates in about Good condition.

Mechanics: The action functions correctly in both single and double action. The single action trigger is light and crisp, and the cylinder lockup is exceptional on all nine chambers. We did not fire this revolver.

Box, Paperwork & Accessories: This revolver comes with a brown leather holster marked “Hunter”. The snaps on the belt loop and securing strap are marked “Hunter” and show tarnish and green verdigris. The holster shows wear but there is no surface loss and the stitching is intact. The securing strap is not cracked. The holster rates in about Good overall condition.

Our Assessment: While the outside of this revolver is less than pristine, the bore is good, and the cylinder lockup is GREAT. This revolver ought to be a tack-driver. If you are looking for a plinker or a rimfire revolver for small game hunting, or just to carry with you out in the field, you ought to give this revolver a good look.

CA Legal or CA Private Party Transferable: This C&R eligible revolver is NOT on the California “roster of handguns certified for sale” and can only be sold to a California resident as a private party transaction (PPT) at our shop in Simi Valley. This does not apply to out of state buyers.
